Package to.us.resume_builder.presentation.controllers

Class EditorController

java.lang.Object
to.us.resume_builder.presentation.controllers.EditorController
Direct Known Subclasses:
EditorControllerTester
public class EditorController
extends java.lang.Object
The main controller for the editor interface. Connects the EditorCategorySelector and the EditorStage together and to the Resume currently under edit.

Example of Design Pattern: Mediator

Author:
Jacob Curtis, Micah Schiewe

      public static EditorController create​(EditorStage stage, EditorCategorySelector sideList, Resume resume) throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
      Constructs an EditorController linking the given components together.
      Parameters:
      stage - The main editor connected to the resultant controller
      sideList - The list of categories connected to the resultant controller
      resume - The resume initially loaded into the editor
      Returns:
      the created EditorController
      Throws:
      java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if any parameter is null
